Aristoteles (§§ 6, 7, 14, etc.) : a famous philosopher, born at Stagirus (or -a), in Chalcidice, 384 B.c., was for twenty years a pupil of Plato at Athens, where he subsequently opened a school. He was preceptor to Alexander, King of Macedon, from 342-335.
